						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Matsyapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 12: 997 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is an inscription of Rājarāja I and it records a gift of gold pot to the god Mahādēva of Tiruchchelūr by Sembiyan Mahādēviyār, the mother of Uttama chōḷa for the merit of her son.</p>						

